  <summary date="2021-06-24T12:31:35Z" status="Introduced in Senate">Dynamic Glass Act

This bill includes electrochromic glass as energy property for purposes of the 30% energy tax credit. The bill defines electrochromic glass as glass that uses electricity to change its light transmittance properties to heat or cool a structure, but only with respect to property whose construction begins before January 1, 2024.</summary>
